    title: "Cardiac Arrest Management",
    cellular: "Cardiac arrest management follows current AHA/ILCOR guidelines emphasizing high-quality CPR and early defibrillation. Shockable rhythms (VF/pVT): defibrillation followed by 2 minutes CPR, epinephrine 1 mg IV/IO every 3-5 minutes, amiodarone 300mg then 150mg for refractory VF/pVT. Non-shockable rhythms (PEA/asystole): CPR with epinephrine 1 mg every 3-5 minutes, identify reversible causes (Hs and Ts). High-quality CPR: rate 100-120/min, depth 2-2.4 inches, full recoil, minimize interruptions (chest compression fraction above 80%), 30:2 ratio without advanced airway. Post-ROSC care includes targeted temperature management, hemodynamic optimization, and 12-lead ECG.",
